"{\"uid\": \"etonline.com-colin-jost-shares-hilarious-foot-update-after-exiting-as-olympics-correspondent-due-to-injury-and\", \"text\": \"Colin Jostis sharing a \\\"foot update\\\" afterhaving to leave his post as NBC's Olympic swimming correspondentdue to an injury he sustained to his foot that led to a number of infections.  Jost, 42, appeared in a video he posted to Instagram on Sunday, and delivered the update like a news anchor while standing on a\\u00a0Mediterranean beach.  \\\"'Dude, are you OK?' That's the no. 1 text message I have received in the past 48 hours. Usually followed by, 'Heard your foot fell off.'\\\" Jost said in the video. \\\"Well, I am actually fine! And despite what big media conspiracies would have you believe, I wasn't 'sent home' from the Olympics.\\u00a0NBC simply looked at my food, declared me legally a leper, and exiled me here, to the island of Malta!\\\"  \\\"Now Malta does not have many Olympians competing this year, but it does have thousands of 15-year-old British kids competing to see who can black out the fastest, and somehow they are all winning,\\\" Jost continued. \\\"They also have this casino behind me, where I have blown the hundreds of dollars I have earned as a surfing correspondent.\\\"  \\\"But the real reason I am in Malta of course is because it was the site of 10 separate bubonic plague outbreaks,\\\" he added. \\\"So they thought I would fit right in.\\\"  \\\"I want to thank the people of Tahiti for their warmth, their hospitality, their generosity and for only occasionally looking at my foot and\\u00a0and whispering 'Chupacabra!'\\\"  On July 26, Jost shared aphotoof his bloodied foot on Instagramafter scraping it on a coral reef.  \\\"This might ruin my WikiFeet score but I just arrived in Tahiti for the surfing Olympics and the reef was excited to greet me,\\\" he joked in his caption. Days later, he posted another pic of his foot -- this time covered in bandages -- after suffering a staph infection.  \\\"You know it's going great when you have been to the Olympic medical tent more than any of the athletes,\\\" he cracked.  In his latest update, Jost shared a health update as well, joking, \\\"Rest assured, my foot is pretty much totally fine. Even though I am not letting you look at it.\\\"  After finishing up his sign-off from the beach in Malta, Jost awkwardly shuffled off, gingerly favoring his injured foot.  Last Tuesday, it wasannouncedthat Jost has taken on a headlining gig at the Fringe Festival in Rochester, New York, next month after palPete Davidsonbowed outto seek mental health treatment.  Jost is also set to host the upcomingJeopardy!spin-off,Pop Culture Jeopardy!, on Amazon Prime Video.  RELATED CONTENT:  Video  News  News  News  TV\"}"